What does this function return?

```ts
function identity<T>(arg: T): T {
  return arg;
}
const result = identity<string>('hello');
```

What is a generic constraint?

```ts
function getLength<T extends { length: number }>(arg: T): number {
  return arg.length;
}
```

Which of the following calls will cause a compile error?

```ts
function getLength<T extends { length: number }>(arg: T): number {
  return arg.length;
}
```

What is the type of `K` in this function?

```ts
function getProperty<T, K extends keyof T>(obj: T, key: K): T[K] {
  return obj[key];
}
```

What does this code output?

```ts
function getProperty<T, K extends keyof T>(obj: T, key: K): T[K] {
  return obj[key];
}
const person = { name: 'Alice', age: 30 };
console.log(getProperty(person, 'name'));
```

What is a generic interface?

```ts
interface Box<T> {
  value: T;
}
```

What is the type of `box.value`?

```ts
interface Box<T> { value: T; }
const box: Box<number> = { value: 42 };
```

What is a generic class?

```ts
class Stack<T> {
  private items: T[] = [];
  push(item: T): void { this.items.push(item); }
  pop(): T | undefined { return this.items.pop(); }
}
```

What type does TypeScript infer for the popped value?

```ts
const stack = new Stack<string>();
stack.push('hello');
const val = stack.pop();
```

