Can you have multiple type parameters in a generic?

```ts
function pair<A, B>(a: A, b: B): [A, B] {
  return [a, b];
}
```

What does this generic function return?

```ts
function wrap<T>(value: T): { wrapped: T } {
  return { wrapped: value };
}
const result = wrap(true);
```
